25/04/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The small right-wing opposition Union of Democratic Forces (UDF) plans to file a new no-confidence motion against the coalition cabinet of Socialist Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev, over the government's social and economic policy. UDF leader Petar Stoyanov said on Tuesday (April 24th) that his party would pursue it after the May elections for European Parliament (EP) members. (Monitor - 25/04/07; Mediapool - 24/04/07)
